So, more precisely, it must be able to support humans until they
can upload or otherwise become less vulnerable. This is far from
indefinitely. But, if a colony can suport itself for several decades,
I think it's safe to assume that it can also support itself for much longer
periods of time (or "indefinitely"). Especially if you start terraforming
Mars (perhaps using nanotech or comets etc).

> That
> means it can't get by on a stockpile of spare parts.  Ultimately, it must be
> able to build all of the equipment it needs to survive, and all of the tools
> needed to make that equipment, and the tools to make those tools, ad
