Greenhouse components should be fairly easy to make with 
even primitive (nano)replicators, or a fairly limited amount of
today's industrial machines (and a considerable number of
prefabs could be brought along). Neither this nor life support 
in general are serious problems, IMO. The really important
issue is whether a relatively small, isolated group can bootstrap 
itself towards a Singularity. With some form of moderately
advanced nanotech, I think it can.

