Not one, but many, can overthrow a government through popular revolt, at least in this
country.  It seems to have not been done.

We might consider reorganizing government to some extent.  While many good laws are on
the books, their unenforcement makes them void.

There is so much bulk and triviata in the law books that almost any legal thing can be
interpreted in any of a number of ways.  There exists contradictory laws.

Here's what makes Washington run:  lobbyists.  This means money.  I'm not saying that
money-archy is not the way the world works.  Money-archy is not democratic, where each
individual has one vote.

A term to describe "money-archy"  might be econarchy, or econoarchy, using conventional
Greek etymology.  Essentially that is Darwinism.  The term is plutarchy.

The operations of our government are in many ways Constitutional.  In other ways, they
are not.

