Lyle Burkhead wrote:
> 
> Is the Singularity inevitable?  In other words, is it going to happen
> anyway, regardless of what any particular person does or does not do?  Or
> is it contingent, i.e. something that may or may not happen?

Absolutely contingent.  Eat the planet with grey goo, and no
Singularity.  But I do think that if the planet isn't destroyed
*completely*, every last human being dead, then the Singularity will
eventually occur - and likewise, with no Singularity, someone will
eventually blow up the planet.  There are no realistic stable states
except those two.
