Making a macro-scale general-purpose assembler would be inherently far more
difficult than making a nano-scale device to do the same thing.  The
difference is that the nano-scale device is working in a universe of
standardized parts (i.e. atoms), whereas the macro-scale device has to
handle an essentially infinite variety of parts (i.e. any possible
arrangement of atoms).

