interpreted by the brain into a virtual representation of reality.  Long
before I heard of Transhumanism, I was fascinated with the idea of
augmenting my senses in order to get a better picture of what the *real*
world looks like.

Now, neuro-scientists and philosophers are increasingly suggesting that the
*self* is a sort of user-illusion.  Great!  Not only is what I'm sensing a
distorted perception, but the *I* consciously experiencing the sensing is an
illusion.  No wonder reality feels a but unreal.

