Gasoline is the explosive driver of pistons in a conventional internal
combustion engine, which prevents battery drain through the alternator.  Any
fuel of an internal combustion engine does so by exploding.

Piezo-electric materials can generate electrical current from pressure, and
vice versa.  Very high pressure, eg, from high explosives, would probably tend
to destroy the piezo-electric materials.

